The paper discusses the challenges and techniques involved in the forensic investigation of cloud-enabled big data storage solutions, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The focus is on Syncany, a popular storage engine for big data platforms, which falls under the category of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC) and database management systems (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the identification and recovery of residual artifacts, which falls under the category of cyber forensics (cs.CY). Finally, the paper discusses the streamlining of the investigation process, which falls under the category of software engineering (cs.SE).
